19:15.589 --> 19:17.678
LAST THING THEY NEED IS ONE
OF US GETTING IN THE MIDDLE.

19:29.168 --> 19:30.995
-I JUST CAME FROM
THE CHIEF'S OFFICE.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.998
I'M AFRAID I'VE
GOT SOME BAD NEWS.

19:35.217 --> 19:36.436
-HOW BAD?

19:37.785 --> 19:39.352
-HE'S ORDERED A
FULL INVESTIGATION

19:39.482 --> 19:42.485
OF YOUR EXTRACURRICULAR
ACTIVITIES.

19:42.616 --> 19:45.096
HE'LL BE INTERVIEWING
ALL PARTIES INVOLVED.

19:45.227 --> 19:46.794
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE BIG DEAL IS HERE.

19:46.924 --> 19:48.665
WE ALL WORK AROUND
HALF NAKED ANYWAY!

19:48.796 --> 19:50.624
-IN THE MEAN TIME
WHILE THE INVESTIGATION

19:50.754 --> 19:51.755
WILL BE CONDUCTED,

19:52.930 --> 19:54.280
YOU'VE BEEN SUSPENDED
WITHOUT PAY.

19:54.889 --> 19:57.021
-SUSPENDED!

19:57.152 --> 19:59.894
WITHOUT EVEN GETTING TO
TELL MY SIDE OF THE STORY?

20:00.024 --> 20:01.678
THAT'S NOT FAIR!

20:01.809 --> 20:04.551
-I DON'T MAKE THE RULES.
-OH, NO, YOU JUST ENFORCE THEM.

20:06.466 --> 20:08.337
-DONNA, PERHAPS IF
YOU WOULD'VE CONSIDERED

20:08.468 --> 20:10.078
THE CONSEQUENCES
OF YOUR ACTIONS

20:10.209 --> 20:12.428
BEFORE YOU WENT AND TOOK THEM,
NONE OF THIS WOULD'VE HAPPENED.

20:12.559 --> 20:14.038
-WELL, PERHAPS
IF I HAD A LITTLE SUPPORT

20:14.169 --> 20:16.606
AROUND HERE, IT WOULDN'T
BE HAPPENING EITHER.

20:34.755 --> 20:37.192
-OKAY, HI, EVERYBODY, HI.

20:38.498 --> 20:40.239
MY NAME IS CAROLINE
HOLDEN, FOR THOSE OF YOU

20:40.369 --> 20:42.328
WHO DON'T KNOW ME,
AND I WILL BE ACCOMPANYING YOU

20:42.458 --> 20:44.504
ON THIS VERY EXCITING
LITTLE ADVENTURE.

20:44.634 --> 20:45.853
-WHAT HAPPENED TO DONNA?

20:47.071 --> 20:49.117
-SHE CAN'T MAKE IT.

20:49.248 --> 20:50.379
-HOW COME?

20:50.510 --> 20:52.207
-CAROLINE: WELL...
-OH, YOU DIDN'T HEAR?

20:52.338 --> 20:54.514
SHE GOT SUSPENDED
FOR POSING NAKED.

20:55.079 --> 20:56.298
HECK, I WOULD'VE
PROMOTED HER TO CAPTAIN.

20:56.429 --> 20:58.953
-THAT POSITION IS ALREADY
FILLED, MR. ARMSTRONG.

20:59.083 --> 21:00.346
-WHOOPS.

21:00.476 --> 21:02.304
-YOU GOING TO BE OKAY
WITH THESE ANIMALS?

21:02.435 --> 21:04.045
-NO.

21:04.175 --> 21:05.655
-CAPTAIN: WELL, THE ONLY
ADVICE I HAVE TO GIVE YOU

21:05.786 --> 21:07.353
IS REMEMBER WHAT IT WAS
LIKE WHEN YOU WERE 17.

21:07.483 --> 21:10.269
-OH, YEAH, WATCH OUT FOR
THOSE TWO-MAN SLEEPING BAGS.

21:10.399 --> 21:13.533
[LAUGHS]

21:13.663 --> 21:17.493
-OKAY, OKAY, LET'S GO, LET'S GO!
EVERYBODY ON THE BUS, OKAY!

21:17.624 --> 21:19.887
LET'S GO! GO, GO!

21:20.017 --> 21:21.541
ALRIGHT, YOU GOT EVERYTHING?

21:21.671 --> 21:24.674
HOW YOU DOING, COOL,
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

21:25.588 --> 21:27.373
I KNOW, I OWE YOU.

21:27.938 --> 21:29.331
-YOU OWE ME SEVERAL, BUDDY!

21:29.462 --> 21:31.899
-THANKS. ALRIGHT!

21:47.436 --> 21:48.916
-DOES THAT LITTLE FAN
REALLY WORK?

22:01.842 --> 22:04.714
[KIDS TALKING]

22:10.241 --> 22:11.373
-OOH!

22:11.504 --> 22:13.941
[LAUGHS]

22:14.071 --> 22:15.421
-I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

22:15.551 --> 22:17.118
-YOU'RE SUCH A JERK.

22:17.248 --> 22:18.641
-IT WAS AN ACCIDENT!

22:20.034 --> 22:21.731
ARE YOU GOING TO
GIVE ME THAT BACK?

22:27.171 --> 22:30.566
-HEY, MITCH, JUST FOUND
THIS ON THE FLOOR.

22:36.355 --> 22:38.008
-DO YOU WANT ME TO GO BACK
AND SIT THERE WITH THEM?

22:38.139 --> 22:39.532
-NO, NO, NO, IT'S OKAY.

22:39.662 --> 22:41.838
WE JUST GOT A COUPLE
MORE MILES TO CAMPSITE.

22:41.969 --> 22:45.364
-WE WANT DONNA, WE WANT DONNA!

22:45.494 --> 22:48.932
WE WANT DONNA, WE WANT DONNA!

22:49.063 --> 22:51.631
[LAUGHING AND OOHING]

22:53.372 --> 22:55.330
-SPEAKING OF DONNA,
YOU KNOW WHAT'S

22:55.461 --> 22:57.114
GOING TO HAPPEN TO HER?

22:57.245 --> 22:59.943
-NO, SAM AND I ARE MEETING
WITH THE CHIEF NEXT WEEK.

23:00.074 --> 23:01.031
-HUH.

23:01.728 --> 23:04.774
WORD HAS IT THAT
SAM WANTS DONNA OUT.

23:04.905 --> 23:06.341
-NO COMMENT.

23:12.042 --> 23:14.871
[SHOWER RUNNING]

23:26.666 --> 23:29.364
-HEY, DONNA.
-HEY, SHARON.

23:30.800 --> 23:33.847
-WOW, A DIAMOND PENDANT.

23:34.978 --> 23:36.502
THAT'S GORGEOUS.

23:36.632 --> 23:38.286
WHERE'D YOU GET IT?

23:38.808 --> 23:40.680
-DONNA: FROM THIS ROMANTIC
MAN I'VE BEEN DATING.

23:40.810 --> 23:42.072
-IF I HAD A DIAMOND
SOLITAIRE NECKLACE,

23:42.203 --> 23:43.944
I'D NEVER TAKE IT OFF.

23:44.074 --> 23:46.512
BE CAREFUL, YOU KNOW THE RULE
ABOUT JEWELRY AROUND HERE.

23:47.077 --> 23:48.296
-OKAY, I WILL.

23:49.340 --> 23:50.777
-HEY, GOOD LUCK.

23:51.342 --> 23:52.605
-OKAY, THANKS.

24:27.770 --> 24:29.250
-DONNA...

24:29.380 --> 24:30.904
-OH, DON'T, DON'T WORRY.

24:31.034 --> 24:32.514
I WAS JUST CLEANING
OUT MY LOCKER.

24:32.645 --> 24:33.733
-I KNOW YOU'RE MAD AT ME,

24:34.429 --> 24:36.126
BUT I JUST THINK WHAT
YOU DID WAS WRONG.

24:36.257 --> 24:37.867
-AND YOU'RE ENTITLED
TO YOUR OWN OPINION.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.435
IT'S JUST SO
HYPOCRITICAL COMING FROM

24:40.566 --> 24:43.133
SOMEONE WHO SPONSORED
A BIKINI CONTEST AT THE BEACH.

24:43.264 --> 24:44.570
-I DON'T THINK THAT'S
A FAIR COMPARISON.

24:44.700 --> 24:46.615
-AND I DON'T THINK
ME BEING IN PLAYBOY

24:46.746 --> 24:48.965
SHOULD HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH ME BEING AT BAYWATCH.

24:49.575 --> 24:51.925
LOOK, ALL I KNOW IS I BUSTED
MY BUTT TO GET THIS JOB

24:52.055 --> 24:53.709
AND I'M NOT GIVING IT
UP WITHOUT A FIGHT.

24:54.449 --> 24:57.278
[WINDOW RATTLING]

25:01.848 --> 25:03.240
-WHOA!

25:03.371 --> 25:04.894
-WHAT WAS THAT BUMP?

25:05.025 --> 25:06.896
-YEAH, THESE ROADS
ARE PRETTY CHEWED UP.

25:09.377 --> 25:10.552
-DID YOU FEEL THAT?

25:11.205 --> 25:13.642
[LAUGHS] MY FIRST EARTHQUAKE!

25:17.341 --> 25:19.256
-MALE REPORTER: ACCORDING
TO CAL TECH SEISMOLOGISTS,

25:19.387 --> 25:21.694
THE TUMBLER WHICH
REGISTERED AN ESTIMATED 4.0

25:21.824 --> 25:24.392
ON THE RICHTER SCALE WAS
CENTERED IN THE CALABASAS AREA

25:24.523 --> 25:25.915
OF THE SAN FERNANDO VALLEY.

25:26.046 --> 25:27.961
THOSE APPARENTLY
NOT ON THE SAME FAULT LINE

25:28.091 --> 25:30.093
AS THE DEVASTATING
NORTHRIDGE QUAKE.

25:30.224 --> 25:31.965
WE'RE STILL WAITING
FOR REPORTS OF ANY DAMAGE

25:32.095 --> 25:33.183
OR INJURIES
WHICH WILL CAP...

25:33.314 --> 25:36.273
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

25:36.404 --> 25:38.188
-HELLO.
-CAPTAIN: MITCH, ARE YOU OKAY?

25:38.319 --> 25:41.104
-YEAH, YEAH, I'M FINE, WHY?
-WE HAD AN EARTHQUAKE.

25:41.235 --> 25:43.019
-MITCH: OH, REALLY, WE
THOUGHT IT WAS A POTHOLE.

25:43.150 --> 25:44.281
IT'S AN EARTHQUAKE.

25:45.935 --> 25:48.285
-IT WAS A 4.0
CENTERED IN CALABASAS.

25:48.416 --> 25:50.723
-REALLY, THAT'S THE DIRECTION
WE'RE HEADING RIGHT NOW.

25:50.853 --> 25:52.246
-I KNOW, THAT'S WHY I THOUGHT

25:52.376 --> 25:54.030
IT MIGHT BE A GOOD IDEA
IF YOU TURNED BACK.

25:54.161 --> 25:55.336
SOME OF THE PARENTS MIGHT
BE WORRIED ABOUT THEIR KIDS.

25:55.466 --> 25:56.816
-NO, NO, NO,
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

25:56.946 --> 25:57.904
WE BARELY FELT IT.

25:58.034 --> 25:59.819
SHOULDN'T HAVE ANY PROBLEMS.

25:59.949 --> 26:01.342
-CAPTAIN: I KNOW,
BUT STILL IT MIGHT...

26:01.472 --> 26:02.386
-HANG ON A SECOND, WE'RE
GOING THROUGH A TUNNEL.

26:02.517 --> 26:03.692
I MIGHT LOSE YOU.

26:11.178 --> 26:12.919
[ITEMS RATTLING]

26:13.049 --> 26:14.181
-AFTERSHOCK!

26:14.311 --> 26:15.878
-WHAT IS THAT?

26:19.882 --> 26:22.624
[ROCKS TUMBLING]

26:22.755 --> 26:25.453
-STOP!
-WHAT'S THAT NOISE?

26:25.584 --> 26:28.064
-I DON'T KNOW, SOUNDS
LIKE A ROCKSLIDE.

26:28.195 --> 26:32.939
[ROCKS TUMBLING]

26:38.858 --> 26:40.773
-EVERYONE DOWN IN
THEIR SEATS NOW!

26:40.903 --> 26:44.080
[SCREAMING]

26:56.310 --> 27:00.314
[COUGHING]

27:10.411 --> 27:11.630
-YOU OKAY?

27:16.460 --> 27:20.247
-YOU OKAY?
-I THINK SO.

27:21.901 --> 27:23.816
-ANYBODY GOT
A LIGHT BACK THERE?

27:24.512 --> 27:25.861
-GIVE ME A FLASHLIGHT.

27:26.949 --> 27:27.863
HERE, MITCH.

27:33.303 --> 27:34.653
-ANYBODY HURT?

27:36.176 --> 27:37.917
-YOU ALRIGHT?
DOES YOUR HEAD HURT?

27:39.222 --> 27:41.007
-I'M OKAY, MY ARM.

27:43.139 --> 27:44.314
-I'LL GET HIM.

27:46.534 --> 27:48.667
[COUGHING]

27:54.194 --> 27:55.543
-GOOD GOD.

27:56.675 --> 27:59.503
-MITCH? MITCH?

28:00.548 --> 28:02.028
-WHAT'S UP, WHAT HAPPENED?

28:02.158 --> 28:03.594
-I LOST HIM, HE SAID HE
WAS GOING THROUGH A TUNNEL

28:03.725 --> 28:05.553
AND HE NEVER CAME BACK ON.

28:08.251 --> 28:11.124
OW!
-OKAY.

28:12.516 --> 28:15.650
-MANNY, TOSS ME A JACKET!

28:15.781 --> 28:17.173
-GIVE ME A JACKET.

28:17.304 --> 28:18.740
COME ON, HURRY UP!

28:20.133 --> 28:21.438
HERE, MITCH.

28:37.367 --> 28:39.152
-MITCH, I THINK
HIS ARM IS BROKEN.

28:48.596 --> 28:50.119
-WE'RE TRAPPED.

28:58.562 --> 29:00.913
-ALRIGHT, EVERYBODY STAY
IN YOUR SEATS, PLEASE.

29:01.478 --> 29:03.263
WE'RE PROBABLY WORKING
WITH A LIMITED AIR SUPPLY

29:03.393 --> 29:05.395
AND I DON'T WANT ANYONE
TO OVEREXERT THEMSELVES.

29:07.528 --> 29:11.140
-I GOT TO SET THAT ARM.
NOW, THAT'S GOING TO HURT.

29:13.969 --> 29:15.405
YOU KNOW YOU MIGHT WANT
TO BITE DOWN ON THIS.

29:15.536 --> 29:17.146
DID YOU EVER SEE THOSE
OLD JOHN WAYNE MOVIES?

29:17.277 --> 29:18.495
-YEAH.

29:18.626 --> 29:23.022
-ALRIGHT, OKAY,
ON THREE, ALRIGHT?

29:23.152 --> 29:25.546
ONE, TWO, THREE.

29:25.676 --> 29:26.590
[GROANS]

29:26.721 --> 29:29.506
EASY, EASY, OKAY, ALRIGHT.

29:36.426 --> 29:38.472
-MALE REPORTER: OUR CHOPPER IS
HEADING FOR THE MALIBU HILLS

29:38.602 --> 29:39.995
WHERE THE CHP IS REPORTING

29:40.126 --> 29:41.910
EXTENSIVE DAMAGE
FROM ROCKSLIDES.

29:42.041 --> 29:43.346
-I CAN'T GET THROUGH TO THEM.

29:43.477 --> 29:46.262
SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED.
WE SHOULD BE OUT THERE.

29:46.393 --> 29:48.874
-MALE REPORTER: REPORTS THAT
A TUNNEL HAS CAVED IN

29:49.004 --> 29:51.224
BURYING A SCHOOL BUS
IN THE RUBBLE.

29:51.354 --> 29:52.791
WE'LL TRY TO GET
MORE INFORMATION...

29:52.921 --> 29:54.749
-LET'S GO!
-HEY, WHAT ABOUT DONNA?

29:54.880 --> 29:56.882
SHE'S THE BEST ROCK
CLIMBER WE'VE GOT.

29:57.404 --> 29:58.971
-SHE'S NOT AN ACTIVE
LIFEGUARD, WE CAN'T TAKE HER

29:59.101 --> 30:00.973
ON A RESCUE, IT'S
AGAINST REGULATIONS.

30:01.103 --> 30:02.235
-REGULATIONS?

30:02.365 --> 30:03.366
WHO GIVES A DAMN
ABOUT REGULATIONS.

30:03.497 --> 30:04.715
PEOPLE'S LIVES ARE AT STAKE.

30:06.108 --> 30:07.457
-CAPTAIN: I CAN'T
FORCE YOU TO COME.

30:07.588 --> 30:09.198
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO FORCE ME.

30:09.329 --> 30:11.418
COME ON, LET'S GO, WE'VE
WASTED ENOUGH TIME ALREADY.

30:31.960 --> 30:33.483
-FIND A WAY OUT OF HERE.

30:57.899 --> 31:01.381
[CREAKING NOISE]

31:15.047 --> 31:17.919
[GRUNTS]

31:18.050 --> 31:19.747
-MITCH, DO YOU WANT
ME TO GO WITH YOU?

31:19.878 --> 31:23.316
-NO, NO, ALRIGHT, I'LL GET
BACK HERE AS SOON AS I CAN.

31:23.446 --> 31:25.057
LEAVE THIS THING STEADY.

31:25.187 --> 31:27.624
ONE FALSE MOVE,
TRIGGER ANOTHER SLIDE.

31:30.627 --> 31:35.632
[EMPOWERING POP MUSIC]

32:03.138 --> 32:04.400
-BOY: SOMETHING IS
WRONG WITH BRYCE, MAN.

32:04.531 --> 32:06.272
-GIRL: CAROLINE

32:06.402 --> 32:08.839
-CAROLINE, BRYCE CAN'T BREATHE.
-BRYCE?

32:08.970 --> 32:10.450
[LABORED BREATHING]

32:10.580 --> 32:13.714
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT'S WRONG?

32:13.844 --> 32:16.891
HEY, LET ME GET IN THERE, OKAY?
ARE YOU OKAY?

32:17.022 --> 32:18.893
NO, NO, NO, COME ON,
COME ON IT'S OKAY.

32:19.024 --> 32:21.504
-EASY, BRYCE, EASY.

32:21.635 --> 32:22.679
-ARE YOU CLAUSTROPHOBIC?

32:23.332 --> 32:25.247
-OH, NO, DO YOU
HEAR THAT WHEEZING?

32:28.555 --> 32:29.425
I THINK HE'S GOT ASTHMA.

32:29.556 --> 32:31.036
-ASTHMA?

32:31.166 --> 32:32.559
-YEAH, PROBABLY FROM
ALL THE DUST IN HERE.

32:32.689 --> 32:35.083
-OKAY, IF HE HAS ASTHMA,

32:35.214 --> 32:36.563
THAT MEANS YOU HAVE
AN INHALER, RIGHT?

32:36.693 --> 32:38.043
IS YOUR INHALER
IN YOUR BACKPACK?

32:38.173 --> 32:39.914
-CAROLINE, HE MIGHT
NOT HAVE AN INHALER.

32:40.045 --> 32:42.047
THIS COULD BE THE FIRST TIME
HE'S EVER HAD AN ATTACK.

32:43.091 --> 32:44.788
-ANYBODY HAVE AN INHALER?

32:44.919 --> 32:46.660
-BOY: NO, MA'AM.

32:46.790 --> 32:47.922
-WHAT DO WE DO?

32:48.053 --> 32:50.142
-ERIN, WHERE'S YOUR FAN?

32:50.272 --> 32:52.274
-CAROLINE: OKAY,
TRY AND BREATHE.

32:52.405 --> 32:54.102
-WE GOT TO RIG
AN INHALER FOR HIM.

32:55.321 --> 32:57.279
WHO'S GOT WATER?
-GIRL: I DO.

32:57.410 --> 32:58.889
-WHO'S GOT WATER?

33:08.290 --> 33:10.118
HOLD ON, MAN, HOLD ON.

33:10.249 --> 33:11.685
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33:11.815 --> 33:13.992
-PUTTING WATER, I HOPE
THIS IS DAMP ENOUGH.

33:14.122 --> 33:15.732
PROP HIM UP.

33:15.863 --> 33:17.952
-OKAY, HERE,
LET ME PROP YOU UP.

33:19.345 --> 33:20.650
-HOLD THIS IN
FRONT OF HIS FACE.

33:21.651 --> 33:23.479
HE NEEDS TO BREATHE
HUMIDIFIED AIR.

33:27.135 --> 33:28.571
OKAY, BRYCE, BREATHE.

33:29.659 --> 33:32.097
BREATHE, BREATHE BRYCE!

33:32.836 --> 33:34.490
BREATH, BRYCE!

33:34.621 --> 33:36.014
COME ON, BREATHE!

33:48.591 --> 33:51.203
[SIREN BLARING]

33:54.249 --> 33:55.903
COME ON, BREATHE, MAN.

33:56.034 --> 33:57.687
BREATHE, THERE YOU GO.

33:58.253 --> 34:01.082
BREATHE, THERE YOU GO.

34:05.391 --> 34:06.218
GOOD!

34:17.011 --> 34:18.230
YOU'LL BE ALRIGHT.

34:19.405 --> 34:23.409
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

35:12.501 --> 35:14.155
-SCOUT TEAM'S
ON THEIR WAY IN.

35:14.286 --> 35:15.722
-LET'S START DIGGING.

35:17.637 --> 35:18.899
-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, SHAH.

35:19.508 --> 35:20.988
LISTEN, DO YOU GUYS HEAR THAT?

35:24.818 --> 35:26.167
-NO.
-NO.

35:33.087 --> 35:35.481
-THIS LOOKS LIKE AN OPENING.
-NO, DON'T DO THAT!

35:48.058 --> 35:49.364
-CAREFUL NOW!

35:49.495 --> 35:51.410
HEY, MITCH, MITCH!

35:51.540 --> 35:54.500
-MITCH, MITCH, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

35:57.242 --> 35:58.547
-I'VE GOT TO FIND MITCH.

35:58.678 --> 36:00.070
MANNY, YOU'RE IN CHARGE.

36:11.778 --> 36:14.607
-MITCH, MITCH, MITCH!
-MITCH!

36:14.737 --> 36:17.610
-WE'RE COMING!
-CAN YOU SEE ANYTHING?

36:17.740 --> 36:19.002
BE CAREFUL.

36:19.742 --> 36:23.224
-MITCH, MITCH, MITCH.

36:26.793 --> 36:28.577
-CAN YOU SEE ANYTHING?

36:28.708 --> 36:31.014
-WAIT A SECOND,
I THINK I FOUND HIM.

36:31.145 --> 36:32.451
-IS HE ALIVE, IS HE ALRIGHT?

36:32.581 --> 36:34.017
-HANG ON!

36:59.695 --> 37:01.958
-CODY: DONNA, WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:03.221 --> 37:04.570
-I FOUND HIM,
HE'S NOT BREATHING!

37:04.700 --> 37:06.441
-DOES HE HAVE A PULSE?

37:07.181 --> 37:09.227
MAKE SURE HIS AIRWAY IS CLEAR!

37:23.241 --> 37:26.635
-MITCH, COME ON, I'M GOING
TO GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

37:32.119 --> 37:33.512
-CAPTAIN: IS HE OKAY?

37:38.212 --> 37:41.346
WE GOT YOU, THAT'S IT.

37:43.522 --> 37:45.915
YOU'RE ALMOST THERE,
JUST A LITTLE BIT LONGER!

37:47.003 --> 37:48.004
-HELP HIM OUT!

37:51.921 --> 37:53.880
MITCH, ARE YOU OKAY?

37:56.230 --> 37:57.753
-WHAT TOOK YOU GUYS SO LONG?

37:57.884 --> 37:59.538
-WHERE'S THE KIDS?

37:59.668 --> 38:01.279
-THEY'RE STILL ALIVE BUT
THEY'RE RUNNING OUT OF AIR.

38:01.409 --> 38:02.454
-LET'S GO.

38:03.237 --> 38:04.194
-LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

38:04.325 --> 38:06.022
WE'RE COMING, HANG IN THERE!

38:06.153 --> 38:08.764
-CAROLINE, CAROLINE!

38:11.637 --> 38:12.942
-MITCH: NEWMIE, MITCH.

38:13.073 --> 38:14.074
-NEWMIE ON RADIO:
EVERYBODY OKAY?

38:14.204 --> 38:15.945
-YEAH, WE'RE ALIVE.

38:16.076 --> 38:17.730
GOT A LOT OF WALKING
WOUNDED HERE, PAL,

38:17.860 --> 38:19.558
WHY DON'T YOU SEND US
ANOTHER VEHICLE?

38:19.688 --> 38:21.037
COUPLE MORE GUARDS.

38:21.168 --> 38:22.691
-NEWMIE: YOU GOT IT.
-ALRIGHT, THANKS.

38:25.868 --> 38:27.305
GOOD WORK IN THERE, HUH?

38:27.435 --> 38:28.871
-SHE'S OKAY,
HER KNEE'S A LITTLE BANGED UP.

38:33.615 --> 38:35.051
-BUDDY, HOW ARE YOU
DOING, HANGING IN THERE?

38:36.531 --> 38:37.924
-THANKS, MAN.

38:39.621 --> 38:41.231
YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

38:42.276 --> 38:44.670
-HEY, NOBODY'S PERFECT.

38:47.063 --> 38:48.717
-HOW DID YOU KNOW
HOW TO DO THAT?

38:49.588 --> 38:51.067
-MY FATHER HAS GOT ASTHMA.

38:53.156 --> 38:54.767
GUESS I'VE BEEN
AROUND IT ALL MY LIFE.

38:54.897 --> 38:56.072
YOU KNOW?

38:58.814 --> 39:00.686
-GUESS I'M SORT OF
LUCKY YOU WERE AROUND.

39:04.124 --> 39:05.604
HOPE IT STAYS THAT WAY.

39:13.481 --> 39:14.743
-HEY, NO PROBLEM, BRO.

39:23.099 --> 39:25.319
[SOOTHING MUSIC]

39:44.033 --> 39:45.731
-JUST CAME FROM
THE CHIEF'S OFFICE.

39:46.296 --> 39:49.212
YOU GOT YOUR JOB BACK
IF YOU STILL WANT IT.

39:49.343 --> 39:51.214
-YOU MEAN, JUST LIKE THAT,
THE CHIEF IS WILLING

39:51.345 --> 39:52.520
TO FORGIVE AND FORGET?

39:52.651 --> 39:54.740
-WELL, WE MADE HIM REALIZE THAT,

39:55.349 --> 39:56.785
THAT LOSING A LIFEGUARD
OF YOUR CALIBER

39:56.916 --> 39:59.527
WOULD DO FAR MORE
DAMAGE TO THE DEPARTMENT

39:59.658 --> 40:02.182
THAN ANY
OF YOUR PHOTOGRAPHS.

40:02.748 --> 40:03.836
-AND WHAT ABOUT YOU?

40:05.925 --> 40:08.754
-I'M WILLING TO ACCEPT
THAT, THAT WHAT YOU DO

40:08.884 --> 40:11.278
ON THE JOB IS MUCH
MORE IMPORTANT

40:11.409 --> 40:13.149
THAN WHAT YOU DO OFF THE JOB.

40:14.890 --> 40:16.414
-THANKS FOR STANDING UP
FOR ME.

40:17.632 --> 40:19.808
-WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GO BACK TO HEADQUARTERS

40:19.939 --> 40:21.157
AND WORK OUT
YOUR NEW SCHEDULE?

40:21.288 --> 40:23.029
-OKAY.

40:23.159 --> 40:26.336
-OH, I SHOULD MENTION, YOU'RE
NOT TOTALLY OFF THE HOOK.

40:27.120 --> 40:28.208
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

40:28.730 --> 40:30.036
-THE CHIEF DID INSIST
ON ISSUING A LETTER

40:30.166 --> 40:33.256
OF REPRIMAND THAT WILL STAY
ON YOUR PERMANENT FILE.

40:34.475 --> 40:35.824
-I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

40:40.263 --> 40:43.092
-OH, HE DID HAVE
ONE OTHER REQUEST.

40:43.223 --> 40:46.574
-WHAT?
-YOUR AUTOGRAPH.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.533
[LAUGHTER]

41:01.807 --> 41:03.591
-DONNA: SO HOW SHOULD
I MAKE IT OUT, "DEAR, CHIEF..."?

41:03.722 --> 41:04.723
WHAT'S HIS FIRST NAME?

41:04.853 --> 41:05.854
-CAPTAIN: CLARENCE.

41:06.551 --> 41:08.770
-DONNA: OKAY, I'LL
JUST PUT "DEAR, CHIEF".

41:08.901 --> 41:10.337
[LAUGHTER]

41:16.604 --> 41:21.000
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
